      • addLinkedWorkbook

        public boolean addLinkedWorkbook(java.lang.String name,
                                 java.io.InputStream inputStream,
                                 java.lang.String password)
                          throws FormatNotUnderstoodException
        Adds a linked workbook that is referred from this workbook. If the filename is already in the list then it is not processed twice. Note that the inputStream is closed after parsing
        Specified by:
        addLinkedWorkbook in interface OfficeReaderParserInterface
        Parameters:
        name - fileName (without path) of the workbook
        inputStream - content of the linked workbook
        password - if document is encrypted, null if not encrypted
        Returns:
        true if it has been added, false if it has been already added
        Throws:
        FormatNotUnderstoodException - in case there are issues reading from the Excel file

      • getLinkedWorkbooks

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getLinkedWorkbooks()
        Provides a list of filenames that contain workbooks that are linked with the current one. Officially supported only for new Excel format. For the old Excel format this is experimental
        Specified by:
        getLinkedWorkbooks in interface OfficeReaderParserInterface
        Returns:
        list of filenames (without path) belonging to linked workbooks
